Data Flow


Endpoint machines (Test PC, DC VM, Client VM, Management Laptop) collect Windows Event logs
Universal Forwarders on each machine forward logs to Splunk receiver (9997)
Splunk Indexer receives, parses, and indexes logs into searchable index
Splunk Web UI (8000) provides search and visualization interface



Splunk Server Installation

Host Machine


OS: Ubuntu (or Windows Server — adapt accordingly)
IP: 192.168.60.20
VLAN: 60 (Servers)
RAM: 8 GB (minimum recommended)
Storage: 100+ GB for indexing


Installation Steps


Download Splunk Enterprise: https://www.splunk.com/en_US/download/splunk-enterprise.html
Install on server machine (follow platform-specific installer)
Start Splunk service
Access web UI: https://192.168.60.20:8000
Default credentials: admin / changeme (change immediately)


Enable Data Receiving

In Splunk Web:


Navigate to Settings → Forwarding and receiving → Receive data
Click New Receiving Port
Set port to 9997
Click Save


Verify listening:

From any machine on the network:

telnet 192.168.60.20 9997

Should connect without error.


Universal Forwarder Deployment

Overview

The Universal Forwarder is a lightweight agent installed on endpoint machines that:


Collects local Windows Event logs
Forwards logs to centralized Splunk indexer
Runs as a system service (automatic startup)
Requires minimal resources


