Installation Process

Step 1: Download Forwarder

On a machine with internet access (Admin Laptop):


Go to: https://www.splunk.com/en_US/download/universal-forwarder.html
Select Windows 64-bit (most common)
Download .msi installer


Step 2: Transfer to Target Machine

Option A: USB Drive (for isolated networks)


Copy .msi to USB
Plug into target machine
Run installer from USB


Option B: Network Share (preferred for lab)


Create shared folder on admin laptop: C:\Splunk-Share
Copy .msi to shared folder
On target machine, map network drive to \\ADMIN-LAPTOP-NAME\Splunk-Share
Run installer from mapped drive


Step 3: Run Installer


Run .msi as Administrator
Follow installation wizard
When prompted for Receiving Indexer:

Hostname or IP: 192.168.60.20
Port: 9997



Create admin credentials (or use "Generate random password")
Complete installation


Service starts automatically.

Step 4: Verify Installation

On target machine, open Command Prompt as Administrator:

cd "C:\Program Files\SplunkUniversalForwarder\bin"
splunkd.exe list forward-server

Expected output:

192.168.60.20:9997

If correct, forwarder is configured and running.


Configuring Log Collection

Basic Windows Event Logs

By default, the forwarder collects basic Windows logs. To configure additional event sources:

File location (on each forwarder):

C:\Program Files\SplunkUniversalForwarder\etc\system\local\inputs.conf

Basic configuration to collect System, Security, and Application logs:

[WinEventLog://System]
disabled = 0
index = main

[WinEventLog://Security]
disabled = 0
index = main

[WinEventLog://Application]
disabled = 0
index = main

To apply changes:

net stop SplunkForwarder
net start SplunkForwarder

Wait 30-60 seconds for logs to index.


