Security Considerations

Current Implementation (Lab Only)

⚠️ For a lab environment, the following are simplified for ease of use:


Default Splunk admin credentials (change from changeme)
HTTP traffic (HTTPS recommended for production)
No encryption on forwarded data (TLS recommended for production)
Broad firewall rules (should be restricted to specific IPs)
All forwarders use same credentials


Hardening (Future Phase)

When transitioning to production-like configuration:


Use SSL/TLS for data transmission (9997)
Restrict firewall to specific forwarder IPs
Unique credentials per forwarder
Role-based access control in Splunk
Enable Splunk authentication (LDAP/AD integration)
Monitor forwarder health and connectivity
Implement log retention policies



